about.summary: PyNGL is a scientific data visualization package with an emphasis on high quality 2D visualizations.

name: pyngl
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.5.0" %}

package:
  name: pyngl
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: pyngl-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://github.com/NCAR/pyngl/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 14a5fc172d4eb166a675c190d1349e5ac46cbee32d0efcc2c0446d47bbce094b

build:
  number: 1
  skip: True  # [win or py3k]
  detect_binary_files_with_prefix: true

requirements:
  build:
    - ncl
    - gcc
    - python
    - numpy 1.7.*  # [py27]
    - libpng >=1.6.32,<1.6.35
    - pkg-config
    - fontconfig 2.12.*
    - freetype 2.8.1
    - expat 2.2.*
    - cairo 1.14.*  # [linux]
    - zlib 1.2.11
  run:
    - ncl
    - libgcc
    - python
    - numpy >=1.7  # [py27]
    - libpng >=1.6.32,<1.6.35
    - pkg-config
    - fontconfig 2.12.*
    - freetype 2.8.1
    - expat 2.2.*
    - cairo 1.14.*  # [linux]
    - zlib 1.2.11

test:
  source_files:
    - examples
  requires:
    - nose
  imports:
    - Ngl
  commands:
    - cd examples && for file in xy2.py; do echo $file ; nosetests $file ; done | tee pyngl-test.log

about:
  home: http://pyngl.ucar.edu/
  license: 'PyNGL Source Code'
  summary: 'PyNGL is a scientific data visualization package with an emphasis on high quality 2D visualizations.'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - khallock
    - marylhaley
    - david-ian-brown
